	<h2 class="subhead font_c">
		 <img src="/images/homepage/icons/write.svg" style="padding-top:1em;display:inline-block;margin:0 auto;padding-bottom:0;margin-bottom:0;width:45px;" /><br/>
		 Personalisation will save you many hours of valuable time and stress…
	</h2>

		<p class="body">Have you any idea how long it takes to individually address each invitation and envelope?</p>

		<p class="body">It's probably something you haven't thought too hard about, but handwriting guest names on each invitation is a messy, time consuming , physically demanding and error prone business&hellip;</p>

		<p class="body">Your hand will ache after a while and the beautiful handwriting you inscribed on the first invitation will start looking like a Doctor's signature by invitation number 32.</p>

		<p class="body">And there's no delete button when you mess up the spelling, and oh dear, now your invitation is ruined as the name won't fit in the space!</p>

		<p class="body">If you're going to personalise your invitations by hand, then you need to be prepared to order a good few extra envelopes and invitations as you're going to screw up some of them. It's a fact. </p>



										<div class="width_66 centred caption" style="clear:both;"id="caption_vellum_cover">

